    "body": "I also have this problem for any contracts imported from the same directory as the target contract.\r\n\r\ne.g, compiling _Greeter.sol_, with:\r\n\r\n`import \"./MyContract.sol\";` \r\n\r\nI get:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontracts\\Greeter.sol:9:1: ParserError: Source \"MyContract.sol\" not found: File import callback not supported\r\nimport \"./MyContract.sol\";\r\n^------------------------^\r\n\r\nError BDLR600: Compilation failed\r\n```\r\n\r\nContracts compile if all contracts are in the same _.sol_ file.  Seems like an issue with the imports / path resolution.\r\n\r\nI'm on Window 10, VSCode, and observe the problem when compiling contracts or running tests via Cmder (console emulator), Powershell, and WSL.",
